So far, more than 500000 soldiers and local residents have moved in to help fight the floods. By the early hours of this morning roads and surfaces of bridges in the Wangyuehu district had been inundated. Most of the 15000 people affected by the flood there have been evacuated to safer places. 56 m higher than the highest figure ever previously recorded. BFN [Text] Changsha, June 19 (XINHUA) -- This capital of central China's Hunan province has been hit by floods in the wake of a succession of rainstorms on the upper and middle reaches of the Xiangjiang River. 